JOHANNESBURG - The Google Doodle on Thursday, 27 April, celebrated as Freedom Day in South Africa, honoured renowned South African composer Enoch Sontonga.The tribute coincided with the country's commemoration of 23 years of freedom.READ: National anthem: Can South Africans sing from the same sheet?Sontonga, died in 1905 at the age of 32, composed Nkosi Sikelel' iAfrika, which has been part of the national anthem since 1994.Former President Nelson Mandela posthumously bestowed the South African Order of Meritorious Service on Sontonga in 1996.eNCA